cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CE 

The paper discusses the use of algorithms for integrating data from various non-invasive imaging methods to get better resolution of data and correlations to behavioral phenomena. This involves the development of a model of statistical mechanics of neocortical interactions and the use of optimization algorithms for training sets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms for optimization, which suggests the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of joint probability distributions and copula portfolio risk management suggests the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the use of algorithms for determining expected duration and stability suggests the sub-category cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
